05/03/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- NATO Parliamentary Assembly President Doug Bereuter said Thursday (4 March) that members of the Adriatic Charter -- Macedonia, Croatia and Albania -- would be the first countries to be considered for membership in the Alliance, following the Istanbul summit in June.
He added that he plans to visit the three countries in early July, to assess personally the progress of reforms undertaken to meet accession criteria.
In related developments, US Assistant Secretary of State Elizabeth Jones said Thursday that the three countries are making huge efforts to progress towards NATO membership.
She was testifying before a US congressional committee.
(MIA, HINA - 04/03/04)
